---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout hideNavbar={true}>

  <section class="min-h-screen px-6 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

      <h1 
        class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6 text-shadow-purple text-center"
        data-aos="fade-right"
      >
        Why One Piece Feels Bigger Than Ever Right Now
      </h1>

      <p 
        class="text-lg text-gray-400 mb-12 text-center"
        data-aos="fade-right"
        data-aos-delay="100"
      >
        Between the anime, live action, manga and global hype, One Piece is reaching a whole new peak.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-gray-300 text-lg leading-relaxed">

        <!-- Opening -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="200">
          <p>
            As I already mentioned, I'm a big anime fan. Naruto is still my favorite.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            But One Piece right now? It's on a completely different level.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Scale -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="300">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">The Scale</h2>
          <p>
            This isn't just hype — the numbers are insane.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            The One Piece manga has crossed <span class="text-primary font-bold">600 million copies</span> in about 28 years.
            For comparison, Superman comics took around 88 years to reach similar numbers.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Anime -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="400">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">The Anime</h2>
          <p>
            The recent arcs have been crazy. The animation, the moments, the hype — 
            it feels less like a weekly show and more like an event every time something big drops.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Real World Impact -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="500">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Real World Impact</h2>
          <p>
            What's even crazier is how far it goes beyond just entertainment.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            One Piece has influenced protests and movements in places like 
            <span class="text-primary">Indonesia, Nepal, Brazil</span> and more — 
            people actually using its themes of freedom and rebellion in real life.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            In some cases, people even used the <span class="text-primary font-bold">Straw Hat Jolly Roger</span> as a symbol — 
            not just as anime merch, but as something representing freedom, resistance, and standing up against authority.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Live Action -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="600">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">The Live Action</h2>
          <p>
            And then there's the live action — which somehow didn't flop.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            The casting played a huge role — 
            <span class="text-primary">Iñaki Godoy (Luffy), Mackenyu (Zoro), Emily Rudd (Nami), Jacob Romero (Usopp), Taz Skylar (Sanji)</span>.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            They didn't just copy the characters — they actually felt like them.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Why it works -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="700">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Why It Works</h2>
          <p>
            One Piece fully commits to its world — no half measures.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            It's weird, emotional, chaotic… and somehow that's exactly why it connects with so many people.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Ending -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="800">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Final Thought</h2>
          <p>
            I'm still a Naruto fan.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            But what One Piece is doing right now? It's not just popularity.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            It actually feels like history in the making.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>